      "blocks": {
        "ai_gen_block_7591c74_taKQg9": {
          "type": "ai_gen_block_7591c74",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
            "description": "<p>Find answers to common questions about our products</p>",
            "question_1": "Is the Maxfoot MF-33 safe for carrying elderly passengers or kids?",
            "answer_1": "<p>Yes, safety is our top priority. The MF-33 features a low step-thru frame for easy boarding, built-in safety belts for rear passengers, and an advanced rear differential that prevents tipping during sharp turns, making it exceptionally safe for seniors and children.</p>",
            "question_2": "What is the weight capacity of the Maxfoot MaxLandau MF-33?",
            "answer_2": "<p>The MF-33 MaxLandau has a heavy-duty payload capacity of up to 500 lbs, easily accommodating the rider and two rear passengers.</p>",
            "question_3": "Can the MF-33 E-Trike handle hills when fully loaded?",
            "answer_3": "<p>Absolutely. Equipped with a high-torque 750W rear motor (85 Nm) and a 48V 20Ah Samsung battery, the MF-33 delivers a 40% increase in climbing efficiency, ensuring smooth uphill rides even with a full passenger load.</p>",
            "question_4": "Is the trike suitable for seniors or individuals with disabilities?",
            "answer_4": "<p>Of course! The Maxfoot electric trike comes with a saddle. It has a backrest. This ensures a comfortable riding experience.</p>",
            "question_5": "Does the electric trike come with a battery and both front and rear baskets included?",
            "answer_5": "<p>The MF-33 MAXLANDAU Rear Drive electric trike comes with a battery, front basket, rear basket and even seat belt.</p>",
            "desktop_width_percent": 95,
            "text_alignment": "left",
